# Signal Lab — Cursor Project Rules

This is an observability playground built with Next.js + NestJS + Prisma + PostgreSQL.

## Quick Reference

- **Rules**: See `.cursor/rules/` for detailed constraints
- **Skills**: See `.cursor/skills/` for reusable workflows
- **Commands**: See `.cursor/commands/` for slash commands
- **Hooks**: See `.cursor/hooks/` for automated checks
- **Docs**: See `.cursor/ai-layer.md` for full AI layer documentation

## Stack (DO NOT CHANGE)

- Frontend: Next.js (App Router), shadcn/ui, Tailwind CSS, TanStack Query, React Hook Form
- Backend: NestJS, TypeScript strict
- Database: PostgreSQL 16 via Prisma
- Observability: Sentry, Prometheus, Grafana, Loki

## Key Patterns

- All server state → TanStack Query (no Redux, no SWR)
- All forms → React Hook Form + Zod
- All UI → shadcn/ui components (no custom Button/Card/Input)
- All DB → Prisma (no raw SQL, no other ORM)
- All metrics → prom-client (Prometheus format)
- All logs → structured JSON via NestJS Logger
- All errors → HttpException subclasses + Sentry for system_error
